05/14/2021,748.2003(b)(5) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,09/08/2022,09/09/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,The youth were cheeking their medication and not taking it as prescribed when the staff would administer the medication.,"Inspector spoke with staff and youth. A new process for administrating medication is conducted. Youth must have one arm behind their back. The nurse has one youth at a time. The Care Coordinator is also observing. The nurse hands the medication in a small cup. The youth takes the medication and then handed a cup of water. The nurse checks the mouth with a flashlight. The youth must cough and say the ""A,B,C""s. The nurse looks in the mouth with flashlight again. The Care Coordinator also checks the youth mouth. This process has improved the youth taking their medication.

The nurses will double check the youth and ensure that the medication has been taken by them. "
